## Description {#details}

This file declares a class that exposes a simple in-memory representation of a document of MsgPack objects, that can be read from MsgPack, written to MsgPack, and inspected and modified in memory.

This is intended to be a lighter-weight (in terms of memory allocations) replacement for MsgPackTypes.

<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Read a document from a binary msgpack blob, merging into anything already</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// in the Document. The blob data must remain valid for the lifetime of this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Document (because a string object in the document contains a StringRef</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// into the original blob). If Multi, then this sets root to an array and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// adds top-level objects to it. If !Multi, then it only reads a single</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// top-level object, even if there are more, and sets root to that. Returns</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// false if failed due to illegal format or merge error.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The Merger arg is a callback function that is called when the merge has a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// conflict, that is, it is trying to set an item that is already set. If the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// conflict cannot be resolved, the callback function returns -1 If the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// conflict can be resolved, the callback returns a non-negative number and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// sets &#42;DestNode to the resolved node. The returned non-negative number is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// significant only for an array node; it is then the array index to start</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// populating at. That allows Merger to choose whether to merge array</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// elements (returns 0) or append new elements (returns existing size).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If SrcNode is an array or map, the resolution must be that &#42;DestNode is an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// array or map respectively, although it could be the array or map</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// (respectively) that was already there. MapKey is the key if &#42;DestNode is a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="424"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// map entry, a nil node otherwise.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The default for Merger is to disallow any conflict.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/msgpack/document/#aa1132fee67332a4c0a707984b97f9b52">readFromBlob</a>(</Highlight></CodeLine>
